  "name": "Whirlwind",
  "type": "technique",
  "img": "icons/skills/melee/strikes-sword-triple-gray.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": "<p>Using a Melee Weapon or Unarmed Strike, you can spend <strong>2 AP</strong> and <strong>1 SP</strong> to make a single <strong>Attack Check </strong>against the <strong>PD </strong>of all creatures of your choice within 1 Space of you.</p>\n<p><strong>Attack Hit:</strong> You deal your weapon damage to each creature.</p>\n<p><strong>Extra Damage &amp; Effects: </strong>If you attempt to add additional damage or effects to your <strong>Attack Check </strong>(such as Class Features or Attack Maneuvers) you must select one target of your choice. The additional damage and effects only apply to them.</p>\n<p>The Attack Check still benefits from Heavy Hits and beyond against each individual target.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>System Tip:&nbsp;</strong>You can add Weapon to use together with that Technique. Select it on&nbsp;<strong>Details&nbsp;</strong>Tab of that&nbsp;<strong>Technique</strong>.</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Technique Enhancements</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Blood Whirl:</strong>&nbsp;<strong>(1 SP)&nbsp;</strong>Force each creature within range to make a <strong>Physical Save</strong>. <br><strong>Failure:</strong> They begin <strong>Bleeding </strong>(1 True damage at the start of their turn until DC 10 Medicine Check).</li>\n<li><strong>Wide Swing:</strong>&nbsp;<strong>(1 SP) </strong>Increase the range by 1 Space.</li>\n<li><strong>Throwing Finisher:</strong>&nbsp;<strong>(1 SP) </strong>If you are wielding a Melee Weapon, you can choose to spend an extra <strong>1 SP</strong> at the end of the Whirlwind to throw the Weapon at a target within 5 Spaces. Use the same single <strong>Attack Check </strong>against this target as well. The weapon lands within 1 Space of the target (GM Discretion).&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>",
